Mozambique, South Africa Mulling Single Foreign Entry Visa, O Pais Reports

-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 
2011-08-17T03:55:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-17/mozambique-south-africa-mulling-single-foreign-entry-visa-o-pais-reports.html
Mozambique  and  South Africa  are
mulling an agreement to issue a single entry visa for foreign
visitors to the two southern African countries, daily
independent O Pais reported on its website, citing Tourism
Minister Fernando Sumbana.  The initiative might be implemented ‘soon’ in all 14
countries of the  Southern African Development Community , the
newspaper reported, citing South African Tourism Minister
Marthinus Schalkwyk.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo at 
 fkaterere@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tim Smith at 
 tsmith58@bloomberg.net  